{
  "info": {
    "name": "03 - Refund Platform Absorbs No Clawback (Case 1)",
    "description": "Case 1 (deductFromDriver=false -> Stripe reverse_transfer=false): platform absorbs the refund, no driver clawback. Approve -> asserts BAP OwnerAsset->BuyerAsset SETTLED (same as Case 2) but the BPP side is a SINGLE SellerExpense->BuyerExternal leg (no OwnerExpense driver-share).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "var envType = pm.environment.get('envType'); var msu = pm.environment.get('mockServerUrl') || ''; var url = pm.request.url.toString();",
          "if (envType && envType !== 'Local' && msu && url.indexOf(msu) > -1) { if (pm.execution && typeof pm.execution.skipRequest === 'function') pm.execution.skipRequest(); }",
          "",
          "// Dynamic refund amounts derived from the real ride's charged amount T (captured by 00).",
          "// rf1 = T/2 (primary), rf2 = T/4 (secondary/partial-2), rf3 = T/2 (04 over-cap: > remaining T/4).",
          "var _T = Number(pm.environment.get('txn_amount'));",
          "function _r2(x) { return Math.round(x * 100) / 100; }",
          "if (_T > 0) {",
          "    pm.environment.set('rf1', String(_r2(_T / 2)));",
          "    pm.environment.set('rf2', String(_r2(_T / 4)));",
          "    pm.environment.set('rf3', String(_r2(_T / 2)));",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
